Relay For Life is a fundraiser for the American Cancer Society where we have the opportunity to celebrate cancer survivors and remember those no longer here. The American Cancer Society is the only organization that integrates advocacy, research, and patient support to measurably improve the lives of cancer patients and their families.

It’s been a minute, since I have done performances due to the work I am currently putting into my artistry, so I am excited to be able to participate in such a moving charitable cause! I hope my brand can always stand for something like this. 

I have a close family member who is a survivor of breast cancer, and her suffering became mine because of how devastating it was to me at one point. But thankfully she is a survivor and she is still with us. These moments really show us the value and meaning of life and how often we take things and people for granted. 
Being a part of this is a very selfless, impactful, and meaningful opportunity. Excited to be there! 🙏🏻

I would say the pain in my chest would be comparable to continuously applying salt on an open wound. I lost my appetite for life because as a human being, when life is lost,  another life is lost 💔
However.. There is only one thing that cannot be taken away and that is the #Faith of the Palestinians. 

For every father, holding his dead child…

For every child whispering, in his siblings ear while dying to 
repeat the final prayer before meeting God…

For every parent looking for the remains of their child beneath rubble…

For every child panicking wondering where their parents went and what’s happening 

There is one thing that Palestinians DO  know..

That God is still with them.
